newsitem.title: USA: FCOJ weekly movement up to 5.182 million gallons.
newsitem.headline: FCOJ weekly movement up to 5.182 million gallons.

text.p: The Florida Citrus Processors Association said frozen concentrated orange juice movement into trade channels for the week ended August 17 was 5,181,651 gallons compared with 5,005,307 gallons last week.
Imports were 247,404 gallons compared with 1,764,239 gallons the previous week, and domestic receipts totaled 96,532 gallons versus 145,664 gallons a week ago.
Retail movement was 931,970 gallons compared with 779,137 gallons last year, while bulk movement was 3,589,231 gallons versus 4,232,027 gallons last year.
Current season cumulative movement was 198,184,622 gallons versus 192,097,943 gallons a year ago.
Inventory was 97,376,812 gallons verus 109,897,464 gallons last year.
The final total pack for the season is 202,353,371 gallons compared with 216,502,392 gallons a year ago.
